name: INTO THE EXOVOID Scene 1: The First Launch
description:
INTO THE EXOVOID
 
The year was 1969, a month after Apollo 11 the spaceflight that first landed humans on the moon, when Indonesia launched its first Space program The Cakra Semesta, sending The Spaceflight Sakti 2 to the moon on August 14, 1969. The initial mission was to land the first Indonesian female astronaut, Luna, on the moon on August 17, also to collect materials from the moon and lunar exploration. 
The program was not a part of the Space Race. Unlike Apollo 11, Indonesia’s spaceflight had only two parts: the command module with a cabin for one astronaut that’s also a service module, and a lunar module.
Spaceflight was launched by a Laju IV rocket from an island in South Java.

Scene 1: The First Launch
Spaceflight launched smoothly by a Laju IV rocket. Sakti 2 Spaceflight spent three days traveling before preparing to enter the lunar orbit and moon landing.
